---
description: Project philosophy — read before any change
alwaysApply: true
---
This is TRASHED, a top-down trash-collector roguelite. Phaser 3 + TypeScript strict + Vite.

THE GOLDEN RULE: src/engine contains generic systems and must NEVER reference a
specific content ID (no "core:rusty_can" strings in engine code). ALL game content
(items, entities, upgrades, recipes, scenes, loot tables) lives in mods/ as JSON
defs validated by Zod schemas in src/engine/schemas/.

Before writing code, ask: "Can this be done by adding/editing JSON in mods/core?"
If yes, do ONLY that. Adding content must never require engine changes.

Systems communicate ONLY via the typed EventBus (src/engine/core/EventBus.ts).
Never import one system into another. New cross-system feature = new event + listener.

Never mutate base stats. All stat changes go through StatSheet modifiers with a source ID.
All tunable numbers (speeds, damage, costs) live in JSON defs, never hardcoded.
Read docs/ADDING_CONTENT.md before adding any item/enemy/upgrade/recipe/scene.
